**Arcana Network Terms of Service**
*Last modified: May 11, 2022*


# Terms of Service


Welcome to https://arcana.network/, the storage and privacy stack for Ethereum dApps and provided by Arcana Network ("we", "our", or "us"). It allows dApp developers to use building blocks provided by Arcana Network SDKs (Arcana Auth, Arcana Storage and Arcana Wallet) for easily onboarding application users, securely uploading, downloading assets to and from the Arcana Store and manage user private keys using wallets. It also allows users to store, retrieve, share, revoke access, and transfer ownership of NFT assets using Arcana Network Storage Protocols.


This Terms of Service Agreement (the "Agreement") explains the terms and conditions by which you may access and use Arcana Network SDKs. You must read this Agreement carefully. By accessing or using the Arcana Network SDKs, you signify that you have read, understand, and agree to be bound by this Agreement in its entirety. If you do not agree, you are not authorized to access or use the Arcana Network SDKs and should not use the Arcana Network SDKs.


NOTICE: Please read this Agreement carefully as it governs your use of the Arcana Network SDKs. This Agreement contains important information, including a binding arbitration provision and a class action waiver, both of which impact your rights as to how disputes are resolved. The Arcana Network SDKs is only available to you — and you should only access the Arcana Network SDKs — if you agree completely with these terms.


