Privacy

When you use the Arcana Network SDKs , the only information we collect from you is your blockchain wallet address, completed transaction hashes, and the token names, symbols, or other blockchain identifiers of the tokens that you swap. We do not collect any personal information from you (e.g., your name or other identifiers that can be linked to you). We do, however, use third-party service providers, like MetaMask, OnConnect and Google Analytics, which may receive or independently obtain your personal information from publicly-available sources. We do not control how these third parties handle your data and you should review their privacy policies to understand how they collect, use, and share your personal information. In particular, please visit https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites to learn more about how Google uses data. By accessing and using the Arcana Network SDKs, you understand and consent to our data practices and our service providers' treatment of your information.


We use the information we collect to detect, prevent, and mitigate financial crime and other illicit or harmful activities by the users of Arcana Network SDKs. For these purposes, we may share the information we collect with blockchain analytics providers. We share information with these service providers only so that they can help us promote the safety, security, and integrity of the Arcana Network SDKs. We do not retain the information we collect any longer than necessary for these purposes.


Please note that when you use the Arcana Network SDKs, you are interacting with the Ethereum blockchain, which provides transparency into your file access, upload and download transactions. Arcana Network does not control and is not responsible for any information you make public on the Ethereum blockchain by taking actions on your file assets stored in Arcana Store by using Arcana Network SDKs.

